  <!-- What Is ENDOMIDFACE -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-ivory">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif text-primary-900 mb-8">What Is ENDOMIDFACE®?</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-warmGray">
        <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed mb-6">
          ENDOMIDFACE® by Direct Vision is a <strong>midface lifting technique</strong> developed by <a
            href="/creator"
            class="text-accent-600 hover:text-accent-700 underline">Dr. Robério Brandão</a
          > beginning in 2006. The name refers to the anatomical approach — entering the subperiosteal
          space of the midface — not to endoscopic equipment.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-white border-l-4 border-accent-500 p-6 my-8">
          <p class="font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-2">Important Clarification</p>
          <p class="text-warmGray">
            Despite the "Endo" prefix, <strong>ENDOMIDFACE® is NOT an endoscopic procedure</strong>.
            "Endo" refers to the internal (subperiosteal) approach, not to the use of cameras or
            towers. This is perhaps the most common misconception about the technique.
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="mb-6">
          The technique addresses a specific anatomical problem: <strong
            >descent of the midface unit</strong
          >. This includes the malar fat pad, the orbicularis muscle, and the soft tissue that
          creates the nasolabial fold and contributes to lower eyelid appearance.
        </p>

        <p class="mb-6">
          Traditional SMAS techniques don't adequately address the midface because they work in a
          different plane and vector. Deep Plane techniques can address the midface but require
          extensive dissection and work in planes that may be disrupted in the <a
            href="/philosophy/modern-face-definition"
            class="text-accent-600 hover:text-accent-700 underline">Modern Face patient</a
          >.
        </p>

        <p class="mb-6">
          ENDOMIDFACE® provides a <strong>direct approach to the midface</strong> using:
        </p>

        <ul class="space-y-2 mb-6">
          <li>
            <strong>Subperiosteal plane dissection</strong> — a defined, safe anatomical space
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Vertical vector elevation</strong> — counteracting gravitational descent directly
          </li>
          <li><strong>Direct Vision</strong> — surgical loupes and headlight, no cameras</li>
          <li><strong>Minimal incisions</strong> — temporal and sometimes intraoral</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Technique Features -->
